reviews.review_text:
One Step Done   what a weird night.  we had driven all the way from NC, only to hang out in this lunar landscape of a parking lot.  I was very new to the scene,  but really enjoyed the parking lot despite a complete and weird lack of shade, anywhere.
listening back to brent's last show I have to say the smokestack closer and victim opener might have pushed him over the edge (sorry bob!)  Chicago is a Blues Town so Brent's own Never Trust A Woman might have really been it.  Anyway, probably reading too much into it, but listening to this show now and its fairly crispiness i have to say it sounds pretty good.  I probably had seen 3-4 shows before this one, then went on to see another 80 plus.  I don't count any more and I threw out all my stubs, so all I can say is THANK YOU!
